Charoen to Sign for $250 Million Loan, Daily Reports

-- B y   Y o g a   R u s m a n a
-- 
2011-09-20T01:50:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/charoen-to-sign-for-250-million-loan-daily-reports-correct-.html
(Corrects president director spelling in first paragraph.)  PT Charoen Pokphand  Indonesia , a
poultry farm operator, will sign agreements for a $250 million
syndicated loan from  Citibank NA , PT Bank Mandiri, PT Bank
Central Asia and DBS Bank Ltd., on Sept. 26, Investor Daily
Indonesia reported, citing President Director Thomas Effendy.
Charoen will use the funds to refinance debt and for capital
expenditure, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yoga Rusmana in Jakarta at 
 yrusmana@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alan Soughley at 
 asoughley@bloomberg.net  